This paper deals with mechanism design and learning in auctions, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multi-armed bandit algorithms to learn the qualities of the agents suggests that this paper could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on optimizing the auctioneer's utility and ensuring incentive compatibility and individual rationality aligns with the subfield of algorithmic economics (cs.EC).
